parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank overflow and leakage can cause fuel to spill on the ground, leading to a high risk of fire and potential loss of life.
symptoms: Fuel spewing from the gas cap input area
fuel leakage
fuel overflow
fuel spillage on the ground
especially when both tanks are full or when switching between tanks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic fuel pump failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vacuum Leak in Fuel Injection Air Plemum
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vacuum leak in the fuel injection air plemum can cause the engine to surge, leading to potential loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Engine surging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank seam failure can cause the tanks to leak, leading to fuel spillage and potential fire hazards.
symptoms: Fuel tank leakage
fuel spillage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel studs can cause the wheel to separate from the vehicle while in motion, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel comes off while driving
the lug nuts back out
the wheel studs break off
the vehicle experiences loss of control or instability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake caliper can cause a complete loss of braking ability, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The front brake caliper becomes very hot
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brake and ABS warning lights stay illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake and ABS system can cause a loss of braking ability, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake and ABS warning lights stay illuminated
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the ABS system does not engage properly
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected acceleration
stuck accelerator pedal
vehicle surges forward without driver input
inability to slow or stop the vehicle.
